<DOC><DOCNO> AP890824-0024 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-24-89 0316EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Romania-Bomb     08-24 0138</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Romania-Bomb,0141</SECOND><HEAD>Ceausescu Dismisses Rumors About Romanian Atom Bomb</HEAD><DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Romanian President Nicolae Ceausescuin a published interview dismissed speculation about his country'snuclear weapon capabilities, but stopped short of denying Romaniahas such arms.   The Yugoslavian weekly Danas raised the issue following months ofrumors that Romania is building nuclear weapons. Speculationheightened in April when Ceausescu said his country has thepotential to manufacture the arms.   ``There always are insane people who speculate,'' Danas quotedCeausescu as saying. ``I do not even wish to discuss this, to lowermyself to such a level.''   The weekly also asked the Romanian leader what he does forrecreation, and quoted him as saying he likes watching the U.S.detective series ``Kojak.'' But, the leader was quoted as saying,``My hobby is achieving socialism in Romania.''</TEXT></DOC>